cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on part-of-speech (POS) tagging of user-generated text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses a neural network architecture, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses regularization techniques, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with text classification, which could also place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
